# ðŸ”¹ JavaScript Array Methods

## âœ… 1. Adding / Removing Elements

* **push()** â†’ Add at end

```js
let arr = [1, 2];
arr.push(3);  
console.log(arr); // [1,2,3]
```

* **pop()** â†’ Remove last element

```js
arr.pop();  
console.log(arr); // [1,2]
```

* **unshift()** â†’ Add at beginning

```js
arr.unshift(0);  
console.log(arr); // [0,1,2]
```

* **shift()** â†’ Remove first element

```js
arr.shift();  
console.log(arr); // [1,2]
```

---

## âœ… 2. Searching / Checking

* **indexOf()** â†’ Find index of element

```js
["a","b","c"].indexOf("b"); // 1
```

* **lastIndexOf()** â†’ Find last occurrence

```js
[1,2,3,2].lastIndexOf(2); // 3
```

* **includes()** â†’ Check presence

```js
[1,2,3].includes(2); // true
```

* **find()** â†’ First element matching condition

```js
[5,10,15].find(x => x > 9); // 10
```

* **findIndex()** â†’ Index of first element matching

```js
[5,10,15].findIndex(x => x > 9); // 1
```

---

## âœ… 3. Transforming / Iterating

* **map()** â†’ Creates new array by applying function

```js
[1,2,3].map(x => x*2); // [2,4,6]
```

* **filter()** â†’ Keeps only matching elements

```js
[1,2,3,4].filter(x => x%2==0); // [2,4]
```

* **reduce()** â†’ Reduce to single value

```js
[1,2,3,4].reduce((a,b)=>a+b,0); // 10
```

* **forEach()** â†’ Loop through array

```js
[1,2,3].forEach(x => console.log(x));
```

---

## âœ… 4. Sorting & Reversing

* **sort()** â†’ Sort (lexical by default)

```js
[10,2,30].sort(); // [10,2,30] â†’ ["10","2","30"]
[10,2,30].sort((a,b)=>a-b); // [2,10,30]
```

* **reverse()** â†’ Reverse order

```js
[1,2,3].reverse(); // [3,2,1]
```

---

## âœ… 5. Joining / Splitting

* **join()** â†’ Array â†’ String

```js
["a","b","c"].join("-"); // "a-b-c"
```

* **concat()** â†’ Merge arrays

```js
[1,2].concat([3,4]); // [1,2,3,4]
```

* **flat()** â†’ Flatten nested arrays

```js
[1,[2,[3]]].flat(2); // [1,2,3]
```

---

## âœ… 6. Extracting / Modifying

* **slice(start, end)** â†’ Copy portion (doesnâ€™t change original)

```js
[1,2,3,4].slice(1,3); // [2,3]
```

* **splice(start, deleteCount, ...items)** â†’ Add/remove/replace (modifies original)

```js
let arr = [1,2,3,4];
arr.splice(1,2,"X"); // remove 2 elements from index 1, add "X"
console.log(arr); // [1,"X",4]
```

---

## âœ… 7. Other Useful Methods

* **every()** â†’ All elements match condition?

```js
[2,4,6].every(x=>x%2==0); // true
```

* **some()** â†’ At least one matches?

```js
[1,3,5].some(x=>x%2==0); // false
```

* **from()** â†’ Convert to array

```js
Array.from("abc"); // ["a","b","c"]
```

* **isArray()** â†’ Check if array

```js
Array.isArray([1,2,3]); // true
```

* **fill()** â†’ Fill with value

```js
new Array(3).fill(0); // [0,0,0]
```

